  <title>What's a virtual colour managed device?</title>

  <p>A virtual device is a colour managed device that is not connected to the computer. Examples of this might be:</p>

  <list>
    <item><p>An online print-shop where photos are uploaded, printed and sent to you</p></item>
    <item><p>Photos from a digital camera stored on a memory card</p></item>
  </list>

<if:choose>
<if:when test="platform:unity">
  <p>To create a virtual profile for a digital camera, just drag and drop one of the image files onto the <guiseq><gui>System Settings</gui> <gui>Device Colour Profiles</gui></guiseq> dialogue. You can then <link xref="color-assignprofiles">assign profiles</link> to it like any other device or even <link xref="colour-calibrate-camera">calibrate</link> it.</p>
</if:when>
